defaultTSSA’s unique combination of roles and grades throughout the transport industries gives us access to planning principles, operating criteria, service management and assessment of efficacy.  
default5
default.2
default              
defaultThe principle of passenger transport planning, when I joined most of 
defaultmy industries
default, was to consider the passenger first, to build service
defaults
default and route structure
defaults
default around their needs.  This 
defaultended
default as transport 
defaultbecame
default private, where service was determined by financial reward and appropriate local, regional or national authorities had to finance any shortfall arising from this mutation.  
default5
default.3
default              
defaultTransport is rarely purely urban, nor purely ‘rural’ – the best means of utilising transport vehicles (
defaultroad or rail
default) is to integrate schedules, making best use of buses and trains.  Types of service and ways to link locations may vary for time of day and day of week – the difference between compelled travel and discretionary travel.  That definition gap often blurs – is someone travelling to pay a Council Tax bill once a month at the Town Hall, a discretionary or compelled journey?
