defaultpossibly
default with no later bus to catch.  This leaves funding authorities with a dilemma – ensuring by subsidy that a route is of sufficient capacity might mean paying excessively, as either scheduling efficiencies would be lost (
defaultraising operating costs
default) or paying for a double-decker to cover irrelevant workings on an integrated operating roster, 
defaultgiving
default 
defaulta
default bus operator money for nothing.  
